But if Flyxion's architecture actually gets built, if we transition to constraint closed systems, if we start living with machines that are physically, mathematically incapable of lying to us because their underlying architecture forbids it, our whole cognitive posture as a species changes.

756
00:50:55,900 --> 00:51:01,600
You're talking about a massive societal shift from defensive skepticism to deep engagement.

757
00:51:02,060 --> 00:51:09,420
If you remove the cognitive tax of constantly having to verify if something is real, what happens to human attention?

758
00:51:09,560 --> 00:51:09,960
Exactly.

759
00:51:10,140 --> 00:51:18,200
Instead of wasting our cognitive energy trying to filter out unreliable content, we could actually start reasoning from reliable foundations again.

